In 1916, William. E. Boeing laid the foundation of
what would become(过去将来时) one of the most iconic names of/in aviation history,
Boeing, an engineering-first company, soared to unimaginable heights over decades.

But it was in 1969, when Boeing would redefine（would+动词 过去将来时） air travel forever.
The release of Boeing 747,
hailed as the "Queue of the Skies" and the "Plane that Shrunk the World",
revolutionized the way people moved across continents.

Fast forward to the year 2024,
the once mighty Boeing is facing turbulence of a different kind.